  "response": "Here's an overview of comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations:\n\n1. United States\n- Comprehensive Anti-Money Laundering (AML) framework\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Strict reporting requirements\n- Aggressive criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n\n2. European Union\n- Unified regulatory approach\n- Extensive Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Centralized financial intelligence units\n- Strong emphasis on international cooperation\n- Harmonized legal standards across member states\n\n3. United Kingdom\n- Sophisticated regulatory framework\n- Proceeds of Crime Act\n- Emphasis on financial institution compliance\n- Advanced detection mechanisms\n- International collaboration\n\n4. Switzerland\n- Historically more lenient regulations\n- Strong banking secrecy traditions\n- Increasing international pressure for transparency\n- Progressive reforms in recent years\n\n5. China\n- Centralized regulatory approach\n- Strict capital controls\n- Increasing international cooperation\n- Developing comprehensive legal framework\n\n6. Russia\n- Emerging regulatory framework\n- Complex enforcement mechanisms\n- Significant challenges in implementation\n- Variable enforcement practices\n\nEach jurisdiction demonstrates unique characteristics and approaches to money laundering prevention.",
